{{see|Ned|NED}}

==English==

===Etymology===
Widely believed to be short for non-educated[sic] delinquent although this is in fact a [[backronym]] and folk etymology. More convincing suggestion is that it is a contraction of "ne'er-do-well", an older term meaning a delinquent.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|Scottish derogatory slang}} A person, usually a youth, of low social standing and education, a violent disposition and with a particular style of dress (typically sportswear or Burberry), speech and behaviour.

